| Method      | What it does            | If queue is empty / fails |
| ----------- | ----------------------- | ------------------------- |
| `add()`     | Insert element          | Throws exception          |
| `offer()`   | Insert element          | Returns false             |
| `poll()`    | Remove & return head    | Returns null              |
| `remove()`  | Remove & return head    | Throws exception          |
| `peek()`    | Return head (no remove) | Returns null              |
| `element()` | Return head (no remove) | Throws exception          |


Why Comparator & Comparable?

ðŸ‘‰ Java doesnâ€™t know how to compare objects

So we need:

Comparator â†’ external comparison logic

Comparable â†’ internal (class-level) comparison logic


Comparator (Most Important for Interviews)
Definition

Functional Interface

Has method:

int compare(T o1, T o2);
| Return Value | Meaning |
| ------------ | ------- |
| > 0          | swap    |
| = 0          | equal   |
| < 0          | no swap |



